{"action": "input", "code": "def fill_colors_in_output_grid(sub_grids: List[np.ndarray], output_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for i in range(len(sub_grids)):\n        sub_grid = sub_grids[i]\n        unique, counts = np.unique(sub_grid, return_counts=True)\n        if len(unique) == 1 and unique[0] != black:\n            output_grid[i // (len(output_grid) - 1)][i % (len(output_grid[0]) - 1)] = unique[0]\n    return output_grid\ndef create_output_grid(rows: List[int], columns: List[int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((len(rows) + 1, len(columns) + 1), dtype=int)\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    rows, colomns = find_all_black_rows_and_columns(input_grid)\n    sub_grids = divide_into_subgrids(rows, colomns, input_grid)\n    output_grid = create_output_grid(rows, colomns)\n    output_grid = fill_colors_in_output_grid(sub_grids, output_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef divide_into_subgrids(rows: List[int], columns: List[int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    sub_grids = []\n    for i in range(len(rows) + 1):\n        for j in range(len(columns) + 1):\n            sub_grid = input_grid[rows[i - 1] + 1:rows[i], columns[j - 1] + 1:columns[j]]\n            sub_grids.append(sub_grid)\n    return sub_grids\ndef find_all_black_rows_and_columns(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[List[int], List[int]]:\n    rows, columns = (np.where(np.all(input_grid == black, axis=1))[0], np.where(np.all(input_grid == black, axis=0))[0])\n    return (rows, columns)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    rows, colomns = `find all rows and colomns with all black pixels`(input_grid)\n    sub_grids = `divide the input grid in to several subgrids by the rows and colomns`(rows, colomns, input_grid)\n    output_grid = `create the output grid with row number 1 bigger than number of rows, colomn number 1 bigger than number of colomns`(rows, colomns)\n    output_grid = `find the kind of colors i